55.8	Theory_of_the_firm	Theory of the firm	According to Ronald Coase, people begin to organise their production in firms when the transaction cost of coordinating production through the market exchange, given imperfect information, is greater than within the firm.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ad/Market-Hierarchy-Model.png/500px-Market-Hierarchy-Model.png
